The Beijing 2022 Winter Olympics is just one month away. From bidding for the Games to the extensive preparations, Chinese President Xi Jinping has played a leading role.  Xi has hailed sports as an important vehicle for improving people's health, an important driver of economic and social development, and an important platform for showcasing a country's cultural strength.The president, a keen sports fan, has inspected the preparation work for Beijing 2022 several times and vowed to present a "fantastic, extraordinary and excellent" Games. Here are some highlights of his remarks about the Olympics: